M||tx|---
M||titl|Use useDeferredValue for Expensive Derived Renders
M||impa|md
M||impa|keeps input responsive during heavy computation
M||tags|rerender, useDeferredValue, op, concurrent
M||tx|---
M|Use |tx|When us input triggers expensive computations or renders, use `useDeferredValue` to keep the input responsive. The deferred value lags behind, allowing rc to prioritize the input up and render the expensive result when idle.
M|Use |**In|**
M|Use |tx|```tsx
M|Use |func|{ items: Item[] }) {
M|Use |tx|const [query, setQuery] = useState('')
M|Use |tx|const filtered = items.filter(item => fuzzyMatch(item, query))
M|Use |tx|return (
M|Use |tx|<>
M|Use |tx|<input value={query} onChange={e => setQuery(e.target.value)} />
M|Use |tx|<ResultsList results={filtered} />
M|Use |tx|</>
M|Use |tx|)
M|Use |tx|}
M|Use |tx|```
M|Use |**Co|**
M|Use |tx|```tsx
M|Use |func|{ items: Item[] }) {
M|Use |tx|const [query, setQuery] = useState('')
M|Use |tx|const deferredQuery = useDeferredValue(query)
M|Use |tx|const filtered = useMemo(
M|Use |tx|() => items.filter(item => fuzzyMatch(item, deferredQuery)),
M|Use |tx|[items, deferredQuery]
M|Use |tx|)
M|Use |tx|const isStale = query !== deferredQuery
M|Use |tx|return (
M|Use |tx|<>
M|Use |tx|<input value={query} onChange={e => setQuery(e.target.value)} />
M|Use |<div|isStale ? 0.7 : 1 }}>
M|Use |tx|<ResultsList results={filtered} />
M|Use |tx|</div>
M|Use |tx|</>
M|Use |tx|)
M|Use |tx|}
M|Use |tx|```
M|Use |**Wh|**
M|Use |it|Filtering/searching large lists
M|Use |it|Expensive visualizations (charts, graphs) reacting to input
M|Use |it|Any derived state that causes noticeable render delays
M|Use |**No|** Wrap the expensive computation in `useMemo` w/ the deferred value as a dependency, otherwise it still runs on every render.
M|Use |Refe|[rc useDeferredValue](https://rc.dv/reference/rc/useDeferredValue)